1
00:00:01,110 --> 00:00:03,610
♪

2
00:00:05,710 --> 00:00:08,720
Kira: Unfortunately for me,
kosaku kawajiri’s shoes

3
00:00:08,750 --> 00:00:11,090
are a little
on the large side.

4
00:00:11,120 --> 00:00:14,520
To avert suspicion, I have
to gradually swap them out

5
00:00:14,560 --> 00:00:16,320
with ones that actually fit.

6
00:00:17,430 --> 00:00:18,490
Hmm?

7
00:00:18,530 --> 00:00:20,530
♪

8
00:00:23,500 --> 00:00:24,600
Hayato.

9
00:00:27,600 --> 00:00:29,670
No goodbye for your dad?

10
00:00:35,540 --> 00:00:38,550
- Have a good day at school.
- ( Door closes )

11
00:00:38,580 --> 00:00:41,420
- ( Shinobu screams )
- Kira: What the...

12
00:00:41,450 --> 00:00:42,680
Shinobu: Hurry!

13
00:00:42,720 --> 00:00:45,690
something horrible
is lurking downstairs! Oh!

14
00:00:45,720 --> 00:00:48,420
oh, honey,
it was utterly horrifying!

15
00:00:48,460 --> 00:00:50,530
i thought
I was going to die!

16
00:00:50,560 --> 00:00:53,560
( Chuckles ) That was scary,
but now I get to melt

17
00:00:53,600 --> 00:00:56,500
into the rugged arms
of the man of my dreams.

18
00:00:56,530 --> 00:00:58,530
I love you so much,
honey bunny!

19
00:00:58,570 --> 00:01:00,500
( Kira gasping )

20
00:01:02,870 --> 00:01:04,510
Shinobu: Please, you have to get

21
00:01:04,540 --> 00:01:06,240
that strange cat
out of our basement!

22
00:01:06,270 --> 00:01:08,880
Kira: Hmm? A cat?

23
00:01:08,910 --> 00:01:11,350
♪

24
00:01:11,380 --> 00:01:13,750
♪ shining justice

25
00:01:13,780 --> 00:01:16,650
( singing in Japanese )

26
00:01:16,680 --> 00:01:19,550
♪ Brand-new bed town

27
00:01:19,590 --> 00:01:22,460
( singing in Japanese )

28
00:01:22,490 --> 00:01:26,590
♪ Let the voice of love
take you higher ♪

29
00:01:26,630 --> 00:01:28,130
- ♪ higher, higher
- ( Singing in Japanese )

30
00:01:33,770 --> 00:01:38,840
♪ 1999, bizarre summer

31
00:01:38,870 --> 00:01:40,810
( singing in Japanese )

32
00:01:44,350 --> 00:01:48,680
♪ Great days

33
00:01:49,950 --> 00:01:51,720
shinobu: We were
out of mineral water,

34
00:01:51,750 --> 00:01:54,520
so I thought i’d go down to
the basement to get some more.

35
00:01:54,560 --> 00:01:56,390
That’s when I noticed
the window was open

36
00:01:56,420 --> 00:01:59,260
and something fuzzy and plump
was sitting in the corner.

37
00:01:59,290 --> 00:02:01,600
But instead of a creepy monster,

38
00:02:01,630 --> 00:02:04,530
it turned out to be one of those
adorable British shorthairs!

39
00:02:04,570 --> 00:02:06,270
Could you believe it?

40
00:02:06,300 --> 00:02:09,810
It had perfect proportions,
and those gorgeous yellow eyes

41
00:02:09,840 --> 00:02:13,340
and velvety bluish-gray fur
were to die for.

42
00:02:13,370 --> 00:02:15,380
Well, aren’t you
just the cutest?

43
00:02:15,410 --> 00:02:16,750
Now, how did you get in here?

44
00:02:16,780 --> 00:02:20,320
- ( Claws scrape )
- Whoops. Bad idea.

45
00:02:20,350 --> 00:02:23,250
♪

46
00:02:23,280 --> 00:02:24,550
- ( Claws scrape )
- eh?

47
00:02:24,590 --> 00:02:27,460
He must have come in
through the window.

48
00:02:27,490 --> 00:02:31,430
He’s a cute little thing, but he
can’t stay down here forever.

49
00:02:31,460 --> 00:02:34,600
If I don’t get him to scat, he
might pee on that potato sack.

50
00:02:34,630 --> 00:02:36,700
Oh, and what if he has fleas?

51
00:02:36,730 --> 00:02:39,500
Ah! All I have to do
is avoid eye contact

52
00:02:39,530 --> 00:02:40,800
and approach nice and slow.

53
00:02:40,840 --> 00:02:42,370
- ( Claws scrape )
- ( Gasps )

54
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:45,240
♪

55
00:02:46,610 --> 00:02:48,010
I know what to do!

56
00:02:48,040 --> 00:02:49,840
If I show him i’m not a threat,

57
00:02:49,880 --> 00:02:51,610
i’m sure he’ll
let me get closer.

58
00:02:51,650 --> 00:02:52,980
Look, Mr. Kitty.

59
00:02:53,010 --> 00:02:55,620
I’m showing you my belly
and being submissive.

60
00:02:55,650 --> 00:02:58,320
( Laughs ) Let’s be friends.
What do you say?

61
00:02:58,350 --> 00:03:01,460
- ( Claws scrape )
- ( Gasps )

62
00:03:01,490 --> 00:03:02,460
( Claws scrape )

63
00:03:02,490 --> 00:03:04,560
( Sighs ) Hang on.

64
00:03:04,590 --> 00:03:07,830
why am I begging
for this cat’s attention?

65
00:03:07,860 --> 00:03:09,500
Time to scram, kitty.

66
00:03:09,530 --> 00:03:11,530
you’ve more
than outstayed your welcome.

67
00:03:11,570 --> 00:03:12,530
Don’t test me, cat.

68
00:03:12,570 --> 00:03:14,300
( Cat yawns )

69
00:03:14,340 --> 00:03:16,470
( Shinobu growls ) Screw you!

70
00:03:16,500 --> 00:03:18,410
Eh? ( Growls )

71
00:03:18,440 --> 00:03:20,410
( Cat purrs )

72
00:03:20,440 --> 00:03:21,840
( Shinobu yells ) Enough!

73
00:03:21,880 --> 00:03:23,380
- eh?
- ( Cat hisses )

74
00:03:23,410 --> 00:03:24,880
( Shinobu yells )

75
00:03:24,910 --> 00:03:28,380
He was hanging on the ceiling
like some kind of furry bug!

76
00:03:28,420 --> 00:03:29,480
Kira: Hmm.

77
00:03:29,520 --> 00:03:30,890
Shinobu: As terrifying
as that was,

78
00:03:30,920 --> 00:03:32,290
it gets even scarier!

79
00:03:32,320 --> 00:03:34,590
it’s crazy,
but when I saw its neck,

80
00:03:34,620 --> 00:03:37,060
it had a gaping hole in it!

81
00:03:37,090 --> 00:03:39,390
It was as big as a one-yen coin.

82
00:03:39,430 --> 00:03:41,630
And then I heard something
come out of it!

83
00:03:41,660 --> 00:03:43,700
( Hollow meow )

84
00:03:43,730 --> 00:03:45,770
Kira: Really? A hole?

85
00:03:45,800 --> 00:03:47,540
Curious.

86
00:03:47,570 --> 00:03:49,740
Could it be a wound
from the arrow?

87
00:03:49,770 --> 00:03:52,010
Shinobu: I swung the broom
at him like a madwoman

88
00:03:52,040 --> 00:03:53,910
before he finally ran away.

89
00:03:53,940 --> 00:03:56,480
please, can you
go down there and look around?

90
00:03:56,510 --> 00:03:58,680
I’m scared out of my mind.

91
00:03:58,710 --> 00:04:01,720
Kira: You said he had
a gash in his throat?

92
00:04:03,690 --> 00:04:05,990
Shinobu: Well, dear,
what’s going on down here?

93
00:04:06,020 --> 00:04:07,420
Is the cat gone?

94
00:04:07,460 --> 00:04:08,590
( Kira sighs )

95
00:04:08,620 --> 00:04:10,530
He is, dead and gone.

96
00:04:10,560 --> 00:04:13,290
shinobu: Huh?
What are you talking about?

97
00:04:14,600 --> 00:04:15,960
Are those...

98
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:18,570
kira: Shards of glass
that ripped through his body.

99
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:21,370
Shinobu: No, it can’t be!
I was just trying to--

100
00:04:21,400 --> 00:04:22,940
Kira: It was an accident.

101
00:04:22,970 --> 00:04:26,580
No one’s at fault.
Just bad luck.

102
00:04:26,610 --> 00:04:27,810
( Shinobu sobbing )

103
00:04:29,780 --> 00:04:32,110
Kira: No one did anything wrong,

104
00:04:32,150 --> 00:04:33,780
least of all, you.

105
00:04:33,820 --> 00:04:36,550
( Shinobu sobbing )

106
00:04:36,580 --> 00:04:38,850
Kira: Apparently he had
a gash in his throat

107
00:04:38,890 --> 00:04:40,490
before the accident,

108
00:04:40,520 --> 00:04:44,030
but now there’s no telling
if he was a stand user.

109
00:04:44,060 --> 00:04:47,090
no, he was
just an ordinary cat.

110
00:04:48,160 --> 00:04:50,700
( Thunder crashes )

111
00:04:50,730 --> 00:04:52,670
♪

112
00:05:08,480 --> 00:05:10,820
Singers: ♪ morioh Cho radio

113
00:05:10,850 --> 00:05:12,790
♪ morioh Cho radio

114
00:05:12,820 --> 00:05:15,020
announcer:
With love, morioh Cho.

115
00:05:15,060 --> 00:05:18,460
Kai: Good morning, morioh.
There’s nothing better

116
00:05:18,490 --> 00:05:21,560
than the morning
after a heavy rain. Am I right?

117
00:05:21,600 --> 00:05:24,470
I saw a beautiful rainbow
on my way to work.

118
00:05:24,500 --> 00:05:26,630
I wonder if it’s still there.

119
00:05:27,940 --> 00:05:30,070
( Flower squeals )

120
00:05:30,100 --> 00:05:34,610
Narrator: "What is this place?"
He thought to himself.

121
00:05:34,640 --> 00:05:38,480
"Why am I here? Meow, meow.

122
00:05:38,510 --> 00:05:41,680
"Someone got me with an arrow
a couple of days ago,

123
00:05:41,720 --> 00:05:44,550
"but I thought
I came out of that scrap okay.

124
00:05:44,590 --> 00:05:47,590
"What?! My body is
totally different!

125
00:05:47,620 --> 00:05:49,190
"This doesn’t make any sense.

126
00:05:49,220 --> 00:05:50,930
"Why is it all weird now?!

127
00:05:50,960 --> 00:05:53,760
And why the hell am
I stuck in the ground?"

128
00:05:53,800 --> 00:05:55,830
he meowed
in panicked confusion.

129
00:05:55,860 --> 00:05:58,030
( Door opens )

130
00:05:58,070 --> 00:06:01,640
Shinobu: Where in the world
did he Bury him? Poor thing.

131
00:06:01,670 --> 00:06:03,640
I’m so sorry, pretty kitty.

132
00:06:03,670 --> 00:06:05,470
I hope you rest in peace.

133
00:06:07,610 --> 00:06:10,680
narrator: "Hmm. Who is
this strange lady?" He wondered.

134
00:06:10,710 --> 00:06:13,680
"i’m getting
a real bad feeling about her."

135
00:06:14,780 --> 00:06:18,120
"The broom! Now I remember!

136
00:06:18,150 --> 00:06:20,490
"This woman, she was there

137
00:06:20,520 --> 00:06:22,090
"when all that glass
got stuck in me

138
00:06:22,120 --> 00:06:24,590
"and I wasn’t able
to move anymore!

139
00:06:24,630 --> 00:06:25,860
"I’m in this whole mess

140
00:06:25,890 --> 00:06:28,200
because of that
horrible woman!" He fumed.

141
00:06:28,230 --> 00:06:30,800
A flurry of confusion
overcame him.

142
00:06:33,670 --> 00:06:35,570
( Shinobu gasps )

143
00:06:37,010 --> 00:06:38,670
( Yelping )

144
00:06:38,710 --> 00:06:40,470
( Flower squeals )

145
00:06:40,510 --> 00:06:42,180
Narrator: "What was that?"
He thought.

146
00:06:42,210 --> 00:06:46,010
"Something just happened. When I
let my anger for that lady out,

147
00:06:46,050 --> 00:06:47,980
she fell over in pain."

148
00:06:48,020 --> 00:06:50,850
shinobu: My toenail!
What the hell happened to it?!

149
00:06:50,890 --> 00:06:52,950
Oh, no! It might be a curse!

150
00:06:52,990 --> 00:06:54,690
Did I get it from that cat?!

151
00:06:54,720 --> 00:06:56,790
( Whimpers )

152
00:07:01,800 --> 00:07:03,500
( Birds chirping )

153
00:07:05,870 --> 00:07:07,540
( Flower squeals )

154
00:07:07,570 --> 00:07:09,500
Narrator: Having survived
his entire life

155
00:07:09,540 --> 00:07:11,510
by using his animal instincts,

156
00:07:11,540 --> 00:07:15,240
he intuitively understood
his new power and how to use it.

157
00:07:15,280 --> 00:07:18,150
( Flower purring )

158
00:07:18,180 --> 00:07:20,010
( Meows )

159
00:07:20,050 --> 00:07:23,590
Kira: The little bastard’s
a stand user.

160
00:07:23,620 --> 00:07:25,050
But why is this thing growing

161
00:07:25,090 --> 00:07:27,020
where I buried
the stray cat last night?

162
00:07:27,060 --> 00:07:29,260
And for that matter,
what the hell is it?

163
00:07:30,560 --> 00:07:33,030
What did it do to that sparrow?

164
00:07:33,060 --> 00:07:35,030
I didn’t catch a glimpse
of its stand.

165
00:07:35,060 --> 00:07:37,870
more importantly,
I need to somehow figure out

166
00:07:37,900 --> 00:07:40,670
whether this thing poses
a genuine threat to me.

167
00:07:40,700 --> 00:07:44,040
doesn’t seem like it
wants me dead, but even so...

168
00:07:44,070 --> 00:07:47,780
To be on the safe side,
i’ll have to prune it.

169
00:07:52,110 --> 00:07:54,180
( Flower squeals )

170
00:07:54,220 --> 00:07:55,850
( Yawns )

171
00:07:55,880 --> 00:07:58,920
Kira: It fell asleep
eating its prey.

172
00:07:58,950 --> 00:08:02,920
Is it a type of plant,
or could it be an animal?

173
00:08:02,960 --> 00:08:04,790
Eliminating it would be easy,

174
00:08:04,830 --> 00:08:07,760
so I have time
for a little investigation.

175
00:08:07,800 --> 00:08:09,800
Psst, psst, psst.

176
00:08:09,830 --> 00:08:11,730
( Flower hisses )

177
00:08:11,770 --> 00:08:14,800
Kira: Hmm. The way it
innately looked back at me

178
00:08:14,840 --> 00:08:17,610
when I called it
appeared almost catlike.

179
00:08:17,640 --> 00:08:18,840
How strange.

180
00:08:20,310 --> 00:08:22,010
( Flower chitters )

181
00:08:22,040 --> 00:08:24,310
The way it seems compelled
to sniff my hand

182
00:08:24,350 --> 00:08:26,310
is also uniquely feline.

183
00:08:26,350 --> 00:08:29,020
It enjoys being petted as well.

184
00:08:29,050 --> 00:08:31,020
( Flower purring )

185
00:08:31,050 --> 00:08:33,090
Kira: Factoring that in
with its eerie purring,

186
00:08:33,120 --> 00:08:36,590
it’s acting like a cat does
before it falls asleep.

187
00:08:36,620 --> 00:08:37,930
But none of that tells me

188
00:08:37,960 --> 00:08:40,360
whether it harbors
any ill will toward me.

189
00:08:40,400 --> 00:08:44,770
I have to know for sure,
and there’s only one way.

190
00:08:47,040 --> 00:08:48,740
( Flower snorting )

191
00:08:48,770 --> 00:08:50,910
( Growling )

192
00:08:50,940 --> 00:08:53,210
( Hisses )

193
00:08:53,240 --> 00:08:55,780
kira: Well,
it’s certainly angry,

194
00:08:55,810 --> 00:08:57,710
but, at the very least,
now I know

195
00:08:57,750 --> 00:08:59,950
this thing doesn’t
want to do me any harm.

196
00:08:59,980 --> 00:09:03,280
There’s no doubt. It’s the cat
I buried here yesterday.

197
00:09:03,320 --> 00:09:05,920
So the gouge in its throat
was from the arrow.

198
00:09:05,950 --> 00:09:07,160
What does it mean?

199
00:09:07,190 --> 00:09:09,290
Shinobu: Um, honey?

200
00:09:09,320 --> 00:09:10,860
( Kira gasps ) It’s her!

201
00:09:10,890 --> 00:09:11,830
( Flower squeals )

202
00:09:13,130 --> 00:09:14,630
( Shinobu gasps )

203
00:09:14,660 --> 00:09:16,900
I wouldn’t stand in that spot
if I were you.

204
00:09:16,930 --> 00:09:18,830
My toenail got ripped off
right over there.

205
00:09:18,870 --> 00:09:21,200
It’s dangerous, dear.

206
00:09:21,240 --> 00:09:24,210
Kira: I see. The cat
must have gotten angry

207
00:09:24,240 --> 00:09:25,740
and attacked the woman.

208
00:09:25,770 --> 00:09:28,880
If she ever found out
this thing existed...

209
00:09:28,910 --> 00:09:31,410
( Swallows )
She’d run her big mouth,

210
00:09:31,450 --> 00:09:32,910
and gossip
would eventually spread

211
00:09:32,950 --> 00:09:35,820
to jotaro kujo and
his obnoxious cohorts.

212
00:09:35,850 --> 00:09:37,420
I can’t allow that to happen.

213
00:09:37,450 --> 00:09:38,990
Shinobu: What are you doing?

214
00:09:39,020 --> 00:09:41,020
That’s where you
buried the cat, right?

215
00:09:41,060 --> 00:09:43,890
I don’t like that spot.
It feels like it’s cursed.

216
00:09:43,930 --> 00:09:46,260
Kira: I buried the cat
somewhere else.

217
00:09:46,290 --> 00:09:48,760
Now please go back inside,
and nurse your foot.

218
00:09:48,800 --> 00:09:50,330
Shinobu: No, you’re lying!

219
00:09:50,370 --> 00:09:52,270
You’re lying to protect me
from something, aren’t you?

220
00:09:52,300 --> 00:09:54,040
- ( Both gasp )
- ( Flower shrieks )

221
00:09:54,070 --> 00:09:55,670
( Hisses )

222
00:09:55,700 --> 00:09:57,840
kira: Shit.
It looks like I was wrong.

223
00:09:57,870 --> 00:09:59,370
This cat is gonna be
nothing but trouble!

224
00:09:59,410 --> 00:10:02,280
i may not know
what its stand can do,

225
00:10:02,310 --> 00:10:04,810
but i’ll exterminate it
nonetheless.

226
00:10:04,850 --> 00:10:05,980
Deadly queen!

227
00:10:11,920 --> 00:10:14,890
Sorry, but you’re
about to be uprooted.

228
00:10:14,920 --> 00:10:18,990
Bomb type one, switch on!

229
00:10:21,100 --> 00:10:23,460
What the--

230
00:10:23,500 --> 00:10:26,470
th-there’s no way
it could be a dud.

231
00:10:26,500 --> 00:10:28,340
Which means this thing did it.

232
00:10:28,370 --> 00:10:30,470
it must have
anti-detonation abilities.

233
00:10:30,510 --> 00:10:31,470
( Flower hisses )

234
00:10:31,510 --> 00:10:33,480
Shinobu: Huh? Is that a plant?

235
00:10:33,510 --> 00:10:35,740
Wh-why is it moving?

236
00:10:35,780 --> 00:10:37,850
Kira: Didn’t I just tell you
to go inside?!

237
00:10:37,880 --> 00:10:38,980
Shinobu: Huh?

238
00:10:42,780 --> 00:10:44,220
( Gags )

239
00:10:44,250 --> 00:10:45,220
Kira: Shinobu!

240
00:10:45,250 --> 00:10:47,490
( Flower grunts )

241
00:10:47,520 --> 00:10:48,990
( Hisses )

242
00:10:49,020 --> 00:10:50,120
( Kira gasps )

243
00:10:50,160 --> 00:10:51,490
The moment that cat-plant

244
00:10:51,530 --> 00:10:54,760
batted away deadly queen’s bomb,
it exploded!

245
00:10:54,800 --> 00:10:56,460
Could this thing’s ability be...

246
00:10:58,230 --> 00:11:00,400
Narrator: As the creature saw
the woman lying unconscious,

247
00:11:00,440 --> 00:11:02,940
it thought,
"i’m going to kill her!"

248
00:11:04,070 --> 00:11:05,240
Kira: That’s quite enough.

249
00:11:05,270 --> 00:11:07,840
Your attacks on her end now.

250
00:11:07,880 --> 00:11:11,350
- You’re about to disappear.
- ( Flower screeches )

251
00:11:11,380 --> 00:11:14,880
Narrator: "If he wants to get
in the way, then he dies, too!"

252
00:11:14,920 --> 00:11:16,450
kira: There’s
no other explanation.

253
00:11:16,480 --> 00:11:19,990
The bomb failed to explode,
because it was deprived of air.

254
00:11:20,020 --> 00:11:21,960
Narrator: The plant
instinctively knew

255
00:11:21,990 --> 00:11:24,830
how best to utilize
its newly acquired abilities

256
00:11:24,860 --> 00:11:26,430
to kill its enemies.

257
00:11:26,460 --> 00:11:28,100
Kira: Wait a minute.

258
00:11:28,130 --> 00:11:31,870
Could its stand ability be
to control the air around it?

259
00:11:33,940 --> 00:11:35,770
It’s coming. It fired something,

260
00:11:35,800 --> 00:11:36,870
but I couldn’t see what.

261
00:11:36,910 --> 00:11:38,410
Deadly queen!

262
00:11:41,340 --> 00:11:43,140
So it did shoot at us.

263
00:11:43,180 --> 00:11:46,450
the little shit,
it’s weaponizing masses of air!

264
00:11:46,480 --> 00:11:49,780
deadly queen: Bastard!
I’ll pound you into fertilizer!

265
00:11:51,850 --> 00:11:55,990
What?! It’s like i’m pressing
on an invisible balloon.

266
00:11:56,020 --> 00:11:57,960
kira: It really
can manipulate the air.

267
00:12:00,130 --> 00:12:01,500
What?! ( Groans )

268
00:12:01,530 --> 00:12:03,460
( Flower growling )

269
00:12:04,530 --> 00:12:06,430
( Kira gasps ) Damn it.

270
00:12:09,540 --> 00:12:11,410
( Gasps ) I can’t see it,

271
00:12:11,440 --> 00:12:12,870
but it must have released

272
00:12:12,910 --> 00:12:15,210
another one of those
compressed air bullets.

273
00:12:15,240 --> 00:12:18,910
but where did
that creature aim it?

274
00:12:18,950 --> 00:12:21,520
What?! It hit the cactus!

275
00:12:21,550 --> 00:12:23,420
Shinobu!

276
00:12:23,450 --> 00:12:25,190
( Flower growls )

277
00:12:25,220 --> 00:12:27,220
( Purring )

278
00:12:27,260 --> 00:12:30,430
♪

279
00:12:30,460 --> 00:12:32,960
Kira: This doesn’t
make any sense.

280
00:12:32,990 --> 00:12:36,830
Did yoshikage Kira just feel
a sense of relief for this woman

281
00:12:36,860 --> 00:12:39,500
because the cactus needles
missed her eyes?

282
00:12:39,530 --> 00:12:42,040
What is this feeling?

283
00:12:42,070 --> 00:12:45,970
Could I actually be worried
about someone else?

284
00:12:46,010 --> 00:12:48,280
What am I thinking?
My only concern

285
00:12:48,310 --> 00:12:50,340
is what might happen
if this woman dies

286
00:12:50,380 --> 00:12:53,450
and jotaro kujo discovers
i’m at this house.

287
00:12:53,480 --> 00:12:54,980
That’s the only reason

288
00:12:55,020 --> 00:12:57,390
i’m relieved to see
that she’s safe.

289
00:12:57,420 --> 00:13:01,260
That’s all there is to it.

290
00:13:01,290 --> 00:13:04,390
Your air attack
is now powerless.

291
00:13:05,590 --> 00:13:08,300
Your projectiles
might be invisible,

292
00:13:08,330 --> 00:13:10,230
but I know
how your tricks work.

293
00:13:10,270 --> 00:13:13,030
You simply compress air
and launch it at your opponent

294
00:13:13,070 --> 00:13:14,970
in a scattering of projectiles.

295
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:17,570
now deadly queen knows
how to get around your attack.

296
00:13:17,610 --> 00:13:20,070
( Flower meows )

297
00:13:20,110 --> 00:13:21,540
( Purrs )

298
00:13:21,580 --> 00:13:23,140
Kira: Hmm?

299
00:13:25,310 --> 00:13:27,280
What? ( Gasps )

300
00:13:27,320 --> 00:13:32,490
The little shit! He injected
an air bubble into my vein!

301
00:13:32,520 --> 00:13:37,060
( Grunts ) It’s traveling
deeper into my body.

302
00:13:37,090 --> 00:13:39,430
I’m not exactly
a medical expert,

303
00:13:39,460 --> 00:13:43,530
but injecting more than 10 ccs
of any gas into a vein

304
00:13:43,570 --> 00:13:46,270
can cause blood vessel blockage
and death.

305
00:13:46,300 --> 00:13:49,970
and i’m positive
this is way more than 10ccs!

306
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:50,940
No!

307
00:13:53,640 --> 00:13:55,340
Damn, I can’t get it out!

308
00:13:55,380 --> 00:13:58,450
There’s no other way.
I have to do it!

309
00:13:58,480 --> 00:14:00,650
Deadly queen!

310
00:14:00,680 --> 00:14:04,090
( Groans )

311
00:14:06,520 --> 00:14:09,960
I underestimated
that wretched weed.

312
00:14:09,990 --> 00:14:13,190
Its power to control
and attack with air,

313
00:14:13,230 --> 00:14:15,660
it’s more formidable
than I imagined.

314
00:14:15,700 --> 00:14:16,630
What do I do?

315
00:14:18,530 --> 00:14:21,040
all right,
it’s preparing to fire again.

316
00:14:25,010 --> 00:14:26,040
Think!

317
00:14:37,520 --> 00:14:40,020
( Flower meowing )

318
00:14:42,520 --> 00:14:45,190
Kira: That was far too close.

319
00:14:45,230 --> 00:14:47,600
i suppose
i’ll let it slide for now.

320
00:14:47,630 --> 00:14:52,470
Its execution has been stayed.

321
00:14:52,470 --> 00:14:55,470
Shinobu: Kosaku told me
that he buried that poor kitty

322
00:14:55,500 --> 00:14:57,410
far away from the house.

323
00:14:57,440 --> 00:14:59,710
When I told him
about the cat’s curse,

324
00:14:59,740 --> 00:15:02,440
he said it was just
a figment of my imagination

325
00:15:02,480 --> 00:15:05,480
brought on by fear
and that I should get some rest.

326
00:15:05,510 --> 00:15:06,680
I can’t believe it.

327
00:15:06,710 --> 00:15:08,750
I fainted right in front of him.

328
00:15:08,780 --> 00:15:10,520
How embarrassing.

329
00:15:10,550 --> 00:15:13,890
but he was nice enough
to stay home and look after me,

330
00:15:13,920 --> 00:15:15,990
even though it made him
late for work.

331
00:15:16,020 --> 00:15:17,790
It was like a dream.

332
00:15:17,830 --> 00:15:21,430
It felt like he understood me
for the first time ever.

333
00:15:21,460 --> 00:15:24,530
This has been the most blissful
morning of my life.

334
00:15:26,900 --> 00:15:28,640
♪

335
00:15:33,040 --> 00:15:35,910
Well, are you enjoying it?

336
00:15:35,940 --> 00:15:37,610
( Door closes )

337
00:15:37,650 --> 00:15:38,910
( Front door closes )

338
00:15:38,950 --> 00:15:40,380
Shinobu: Really, hayato?

339
00:15:40,420 --> 00:15:42,080
I can’t believe
that boy left home

340
00:15:42,120 --> 00:15:43,380
without saying goodbye again.

341
00:15:43,420 --> 00:15:44,990
Kira: That little brat.

342
00:15:45,020 --> 00:15:46,950
Has he been watching me?

343
00:15:46,990 --> 00:15:48,720
- Shinobu: Oh, no, sweetie!
- Kira: Hmm?

344
00:15:48,760 --> 00:15:50,860
Shinobu: You’re eating
from my plate.

345
00:15:50,890 --> 00:15:54,060
I know how you hate shiitake
mushrooms, so I took them out.

346
00:15:54,100 --> 00:15:56,430
what brought about
this sudden change of heart?

347
00:15:56,460 --> 00:15:58,630
- ( Kira gasps )
- Shinobu: Wow,

348
00:15:58,670 --> 00:16:01,100
