more than half of mine.

349
00:16:01,140 --> 00:16:03,600
( Laughs )
But don’t get me wrong.

350
00:16:03,640 --> 00:16:06,940
I’m positively thrilled
to see you wolfing them down.

351
00:16:06,980 --> 00:16:09,740
They’re not so bad when you
give them a chance, are they?

352
00:16:09,780 --> 00:16:11,510
Kira: Yeah.

353
00:16:15,450 --> 00:16:18,090
All right, then.
I’m heading out.

354
00:16:18,120 --> 00:16:20,620
Shinobu: I hope you have
a good day, sweetie pie.

355
00:16:20,660 --> 00:16:23,530
( Sighs )

356
00:16:23,560 --> 00:16:25,960
( Sighing )

357
00:16:29,830 --> 00:16:31,030
( Door opens )

358
00:16:31,070 --> 00:16:32,030
- ( Door closes )
- eh?

359
00:16:32,070 --> 00:16:34,700
( Sighs )

360
00:16:34,740 --> 00:16:36,840
Aww. That’s too bad.

361
00:16:36,870 --> 00:16:39,040
A goodbye kiss
would have been nice.

362
00:16:39,070 --> 00:16:42,680
Although, I feel as though
we’re closer than ever,

363
00:16:42,710 --> 00:16:43,840
and before long,

364
00:16:43,880 --> 00:16:46,050
my seductive love
will overwhelm him.

365
00:16:49,550 --> 00:16:52,490
Hayato: He put his shoes on
with a shoehorn,

366
00:16:52,520 --> 00:16:56,760
and he was definitely wearing
25.5-centimeter-sized shoes.

367
00:16:56,790 --> 00:17:00,160
Why does he have shoes
that are two different sizes?

368
00:17:00,190 --> 00:17:03,900
Even weirder, mom and dad are
getting along better than ever,

369
00:17:03,930 --> 00:17:05,900
and he scarfed down
those mushrooms

370
00:17:05,930 --> 00:17:07,500
even though he hates them.

371
00:17:09,500 --> 00:17:11,070
Hmph. This is also bizarre.

372
00:17:11,110 --> 00:17:12,970
why in the world
would he need to practice

373
00:17:13,010 --> 00:17:15,810
writing his name
over and over again?

374
00:17:15,840 --> 00:17:18,180
And then there’s what
I saw happen last night.

375
00:17:18,210 --> 00:17:22,180
( Tape scans )

376
00:17:25,950 --> 00:17:28,890
I kept replaying the footage,
but that’s just a pot of dirt.

377
00:17:28,920 --> 00:17:30,120
What could he be doing

378
00:17:30,160 --> 00:17:32,630
with that much soil
and a bag of cat food?

379
00:17:32,660 --> 00:17:35,960
Then he goes into the closet
like everything’s normal.

380
00:17:38,670 --> 00:17:40,600
♪

381
00:17:50,980 --> 00:17:51,950
Hmm.

382
00:17:51,980 --> 00:17:52,910
Eh?

383
00:17:56,020 --> 00:17:58,220
( Children laugh )

384
00:17:58,250 --> 00:18:00,790
Kira: They’re all wearing hats.

385
00:18:00,820 --> 00:18:03,560
is that part
of their dress code?

386
00:18:03,590 --> 00:18:05,130
What is this?

387
00:18:05,160 --> 00:18:07,900
I’m getting a strange feeling.

388
00:18:09,260 --> 00:18:10,700
Hayato: The attic.

389
00:18:22,740 --> 00:18:23,680
Hmm?

390
00:18:26,780 --> 00:18:29,880
Whoa. Oh, man, that’s weird.

391
00:18:29,920 --> 00:18:31,750
I wonder what that thing is.

392
00:18:31,790 --> 00:18:32,920
Freaky.

393
00:18:32,950 --> 00:18:34,220
It’s way too dark in here.

394
00:18:34,260 --> 00:18:35,290
I can’t make it out.

395
00:18:46,940 --> 00:18:48,000
Kira: Hmm?

396
00:18:48,040 --> 00:18:50,540
Hayato: There. It’s that bag.

397
00:18:51,910 --> 00:18:53,140
- ( Flower rustling )
- huh?

398
00:19:00,720 --> 00:19:01,820
Wha--

399
00:19:01,850 --> 00:19:03,780
that plant is moving.

400
00:19:03,820 --> 00:19:05,190
No, that’s not a plant.

401
00:19:05,220 --> 00:19:08,790
It has eyes, and it’s
looking right at me!

402
00:19:08,820 --> 00:19:13,090
Hang on! Could that bag of
cat food be for this creature?

403
00:19:13,130 --> 00:19:15,260
Shinobu: I didn’t expect you
back so soon, honey.

404
00:19:15,300 --> 00:19:18,100
Did you forget something? Ooh!

405
00:19:18,130 --> 00:19:21,140
Did you realize you left without
giving me a goodbye kiss?

406
00:19:21,170 --> 00:19:22,140
Kira: No.

407
00:19:22,170 --> 00:19:23,810
Shinobu: Aww. Then what is it?

408
00:19:23,840 --> 00:19:25,770
I can get it for you
if you want.

409
00:19:25,810 --> 00:19:27,210
Kira: No. I’ll do it myself.

410
00:19:27,240 --> 00:19:29,680
Hayato: Why the heck
did he come back?

411
00:19:29,710 --> 00:19:30,810
( Gasps ) Oh, no!

412
00:19:30,850 --> 00:19:33,080
- ( Flower meows )
- Hayato: Huh?!

413
00:19:33,110 --> 00:19:36,020
♪

414
00:19:36,050 --> 00:19:39,090
Guh! What did
this plant do to me?

415
00:19:39,120 --> 00:19:41,220
( Groans ) What are
these weird things on me?

416
00:19:41,260 --> 00:19:42,790
It’s like i’m being strangled

417
00:19:42,820 --> 00:19:45,060
by some kind of invisible,
inflatable shackles.

418
00:19:45,090 --> 00:19:47,830
i’m being pinned
to the air by the air itself.

419
00:19:47,860 --> 00:19:49,860
( Stairs creaking )

420
00:19:49,900 --> 00:19:51,670
He’s coming up the stairs.

421
00:19:51,700 --> 00:19:52,770
I’ve gotta get free.

422
00:19:52,800 --> 00:19:53,970
( Flower purrs )

423
00:19:56,200 --> 00:19:57,210
Hayato: Huh?

424
00:19:57,240 --> 00:19:58,740
( Yelps )

425
00:19:59,810 --> 00:20:02,040
Kira: That came from the attic.

426
00:20:02,080 --> 00:20:04,680
I knew that brat
was up to something!

427
00:20:04,710 --> 00:20:06,150
Hayato: It hauled off
and attacked me

428
00:20:06,180 --> 00:20:07,920
when I tried
to shut the window.

429
00:20:07,950 --> 00:20:11,250
does that mean
it needs sunlight to move?

430
00:20:11,290 --> 00:20:12,690
That’s it!

431
00:20:12,720 --> 00:20:14,720
If i’m being held
by masses of air...

432
00:20:15,990 --> 00:20:18,290
♪

433
00:20:23,930 --> 00:20:27,100
Awesome. So the sunlight
was fueling it.

434
00:20:45,290 --> 00:20:46,290
( Kira sighs )

435
00:20:46,320 --> 00:20:47,920
That noise.

436
00:20:50,020 --> 00:20:51,390
What’s going on here?

437
00:20:51,430 --> 00:20:54,300
did the feral cat try
to get its food from the shelf

438
00:20:54,330 --> 00:20:56,260
and end up spilling it
on the floor?

439
00:20:56,300 --> 00:20:57,730
I thought the lack of sunlight

440
00:20:57,770 --> 00:20:59,300
would keep it calm
for the time being,

441
00:20:59,330 --> 00:21:03,040
but traces of light are
seeping in through the window.

442
00:21:03,070 --> 00:21:05,240
Still,

443
00:21:05,270 --> 00:21:08,380
I thought hayato may have
rummaged around up here,

444
00:21:08,410 --> 00:21:11,410
but I guess I could
chalk that up to overthinking.

445
00:21:11,450 --> 00:21:13,480
That said, had that little brat

446
00:21:13,510 --> 00:21:16,220
discovered the truth
about who I really am,

447
00:21:16,250 --> 00:21:19,420
then I would have had no choice
but to put an end to his life.

448
00:21:19,450 --> 00:21:21,390
♪

449
00:21:25,290 --> 00:21:26,960
( Hayato gasping )

450
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:29,100
Somehow he’s wearing
my dad’s face,

451
00:21:29,130 --> 00:21:30,770
but that’s not my dad.

452
00:21:30,800 --> 00:21:32,300
Who is that guy?

453
00:21:32,330 --> 00:21:34,770
Wh-why is he here?

454
00:21:34,800 --> 00:21:36,040
What does he want?

455
00:21:39,370 --> 00:21:41,310
♪

456
